curam.util.cache

Class LeastRecentlyUsedCache<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • curam.util.cache.LeastRecentlyUsedCache<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - Key.
    V - Value.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<K,V>

    public class LeastRecentlyUsedCache<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Map<K,V>
    A simple hash map based least recently used (LRU) cache. If the maximum cache size is reduced this cache does not actively try to remove excess items from the cache. Items will only be purged when new items are written to the cache in accordance with the behavior of the linked hash map. This cache is not thread-safe
